76561198030069024,Recommended,318220,12651068,"Posted: 26 October, 2014",all,DeadlyPrivate,"I want to point out that Enforcer: Police Crime Action is like calling the Half Life Series Scientist: Atoms Destruction Wait. And yet it is still a much better title (and game) Then any of the ""Simulation"" Games released for the purpose of a quick cash grab.It's simple. You play as a police officer, male or female, and are tasked with the daily routines of being said police officer. You go do a shift by beginning with a mundane mission and will either get interrupted with a more exciting mission or just simply go through the mission and gain points. Points mean you are promoted and get money, thus allowing you to spend it on your house. The closest comparision I have is True Crime: New York City in terms of random missions and being tasked with being a police officer.The game doesn't look impressive, but it get's the job done. It has good character and vehicle animations that allow you to tell what a character is doing and what they plan. The appeal of just going through the daily life of a police officer is a welcome compromise between the hardcore idea of being an officer (Swat series) To the matienince of health and hunger levels (Deadly Premonition).The worst part about this game is that it feels cheap. The love for this game the developers gave to it is clear, and I enjoy the experience thus far, but there are a lot of times where I find cars flipped over for no reason, the camera constantly get's stuck to one position and once someone screams you will hear that scream throughout your shift like that victim is haunting your soul. If given more assets and time, this game could honestly be as good as Euro Truck SImulator in providing for a niche audience.WOULD I RECOMMEND THIS GAME: YESDespite the cheap look this game has, it is a game with a lot of love and detail put into it that already feels like a unique experience.SUGGESTIONS TO DEVS: Focus more on bringing in the social life for the protagionist; I actually felt like this town could be given a lot more history and more characters that you could interact with."
