,Not Recommended,318220,12668963,"Posted: 28 October, 2014",all,Krazburg,"Edit: keep in mind I made this review a decent amount of time ago, some of the problems have been fixed such as your car getting damaged while entering places like the gas station after the map was entirely redesigned, however many other problems mentioned still persistLet me start off by saying this game shows potential, however with that beign said, this game is not a finished product.The game has a number of problems that need to be fixed before it can truly be considered a worthwhile purchaseone of the first problems I noticed while playing the game is that, at least in the starting region, driving onto the platform for the gas station will damage your car, there is literally no way around this from what I have seen, this also occurs in other locations around the city such as the repair station (or whatever it is called). Furthermore the missions are often rather repetative as the criminals will often spawn in the same locations every time. In addition there is literally no incentive to bring the criminals back alive (if they have their gun drawn) you recieve the same points for killing the criminal as you do for brining them back alive (unless they dont have their gun drawn, points are lost for shooting at them).  As well despite the several distinct regions in the game, they all feel almost entirely bland as they are rife with either unenterable buildings, or land with nothing on it. Another thing that I must complain about is the fact that shooting vehichles does literally NOTHING, if you shoot at a vehichle it will not do any damage to the vehichle or the driver, also problamatic is the fact that if you shoot at a civilian vehichle, no points are deducted. Another problem is that if you simply quit and reload your game, your stress level will be reset and your sleep and hunger levels are also almost enitrely reset, which removes the necessity to take anytime off. There are also rampant glitches, such as the fact that the main city (or at least the one your house is in the region of) is rife with invisible potholes on the streets that will do damage to your car if you go over them at too high a speed and possibly even send your vehichle flying. As well I have noticed sometimes that there will randomly be vehichles just sort of floating in the air. I have also noticed that sometimes in the city various vehichles will run into each other for no apparent reason, maybe it is just the drunk drivers but I dont know.Overall, I think that if the problems with this game are fixed it could be a good or maybe even a great game, I really do like the concept of a game where you play as a police officer as it has not been done very often, however until they fix the problems listed and the many more that I probably didnt notice or think to write about, then it is not really a worthwhile purchaseUPDATE: they are improving the game however, so hopefully soon they will fix the bugs that currently plague the game"
