76561198048091979,Recommended,318220,14084830,"Posted: 20 January, 2015",all,Prometheus Unbound,"When i first played this game it was... Well, not good. Dont want to say it was awful.I have come back to it after a few months and it has radically improved.The graphics are not gorgeous. In fact they would not look out of place in early Xbox games at points. So if you are looking for good look this is not it. And frankly, asking for good graphics in something that is a simulation game of this type is just silly.Which brings me to my next point: I have seen some mention that the game gets pretty dull after some time playing. They are not wrong. However, once again, this IS a sim game that attempts to simulate a real life job. And much like its counterparts in the career simulation genre, things are going to get repetetive at times. Just like a real life career. Anyone who has played a truck simulator will have hit that issue where they feel bored, even if you are a trucking fan, like me. And that is to say nothing of my second favourite Farming Simulator. Sorry but real policing is not all gun fights and car chases.Bugs. It has some small ones that unless you are someone who is easily annoyed or bugged (Badum Tsh!) by such things, you will not notice them.What you get here is something that attempts to bring you the day to day grind of a police officer. Even the boring stuff (Which i personally like to see and do) such as traffic policing.Could this be better? Sure. But what it is right now is good considering the small time it has been around.So, dont expect high octane chases, and movie style policing. Its a simulation. And dont expect AAA graphics."
