,Recommended,318220,20135790,"Posted: 30 December, 2015",all,This Is Dark Wolf,"As much as I watched this game receive a lot of negative publicity when it first launched, all the glitches, the game breaking glitches, and so on. Just about yesterday did I really give this title a chance. Now I am addicted to it. For some odd reason. Allow me to give some Positives and Negatives on the game. So you can decide to make your purchase.Positives: -Plenty of Dispatch Missions to take advantage of, which are Challengings and Fun.-Your Police Vehicle has many customization options.-Wide vast area with much to explore.-Plenty of criminals to arrest.-Responsive Controls.-Driving feels very fluent, but takes time to get used to.-Music is actually very good.-Voice acting is on point.-There is always something to do, even when there are no missions available.-Ranking up feels rewarding as you get an increase in pay.-Weather & Night to Day transitions are wonderfully done.-You are able to decorate and buy new things for your home.Negatives: -Aiming can be a chore to pull off, when you are about to get shot.-Sometimes when doing routine checks on cars, the person driving the car will run sometimes, also very far.-When you arrest someone, you are forced to walk. When you want to put them in your car, especially if they run a far distance, walking takes forever to get back to your car which will inspire you to call police dispatch to lighten the burden.-When finished with routine missions, entering the police station for a warrant based on a mission is a problem. When you step back outside the station, the game forces another routine mission on you, removing the perp from the map. Making it difficult to find where they are again. Unless Dispatch decides to update you on their location, which can take a terribly long time.-illegally parked cars don't spawn often, unless you quit, and restart the game. So when asked to ticket illegally parked cars, there are usually none in the street. There is a way around this by ticketing cars on the street by checking their license plates, and ticketing them that way. Its the only way around it.-You take no damage by getting hit by cars. They usually flip over you. Also you cannot kill a pedestrian by hitting them.-You can only arrest one person at a time. When you're after two perps, you have to dispatch the one first, while the other has the chance to escape as you cannot go after them when you have someone handcuffed.-Sometimes Dispatch missions never show up. Because of a game glitch. You have to sleep 8 hours & restart the game. The glitch is caused by the Stress meter being too low. The game gets confused and doesn't turn back Dispatch calls on.-AI pedestrians have a habit of endlessly walking into vehicles, perps in houses run endlessly into the wall, or the door with their body peeking out of the door when you try to arrest them.-The game has a bad habit of throwing you missions even after your shift is over. They should stop. Because when you end your shift with a mission active, even if its routine, you are penalized points. Which you need to rank up.Even with the negatives I think the game is still very enjoyable. Regardless, its up to the buyer. Happy New Year everyone."
