,Recommended,318220,14088447,"Posted: 20 January, 2015",all,SOCOMpro12,"I have found the best way to describe this game. Whilst going through this page and looking at reviews, I figured I should try it. It was on sale and I said to myself ""Why not?"" I personally am a very very very large fan of the police genre of gaming (My favorite games being the SWAT Series, especially SWAT 4, LCPDFR from GTA 4 and various other examples) and while I am very biased in my opinion, which is why it is my opinion, I feel compelled to say that I can see the arguments on both sides. Yes, this game is buggy in various ways (Though not as many as I read about. Maybe I was lucky.) And yes it does have questionable graphics. But this game, to me at least, was not made for the general population. It was made for the people who specifically like to play regular cops and aren't all about the shooting and explosions life styles (I realize the hypocritial way I said SWAT 4 was my favorite police genre game, back off xD). This game has an outstanding amount of minute details. So while I do recommend this game, I recommend it to a very small percent of gamers. If you want a game that's about shooting and explosions then this is not for you. Whilst I love explosions and shooting myself, it's a nice change of pace. And yes, the devs do update this game (As shown by the police motorcycle) but at the same time it is a small dev team so you have to accept some problems. All in all I feel this game was made for me and some other small percentage of gamers. If you are truly stuck on if you should buy this or not, I recommend watching gaming reviews and not someone whose messing with the engine of the game and make up your mind for yourself."
76561198143449385,Recommended,318220,13918344,"Posted: 9 January, 2015",all,AngryScotsman,"This game has serious potential. The amount of people out there looking for a genuine (and playable) police simulator is a high number; this game is for every one of them. It is definetly a working progress, and the developers need to fix a lot of things and add more into this simulator:- AI must be fixed... when someone decides to run away from you, your thoughts are ""yes, finally a chase"" and then they end up running into a wall or car and don't proceed. This ruined a fair few moments for me.-More (and fixed) car chases. Car persuits are a big pro to police games, and this game just needs to up that. When a car fails to stop in this game, it drives far too slow, you want a car persuit to be fast and action filled, not at 25mph on a more or less straight road.- Fixed sirens. The siren/ lights (on police vehicles) in this game is better than most others. Having said that, there could be A LOT more done to make this system more lifelike.- Animations. The game is seriously lacking in animations when something happens in-game e.g. after you shoot and kill a suspect, or find any injured person, the protocol is to phone for an ambulance. Once pressing the ambulance button the cop states into the radio that an ambulance is needed. Then a still frame of the police station shows on screen along with the allocated points for what you have done. That is just one example of many animatons that are lacking.- Fellow cops. For a POLICE simulator, there isn't enough police-you are litterally the only cop in the game. It would be nice to see other patrol cars patrolling and to be able to call for backup when you are under fire from multiple people.- Different scenarios (and locations). After a while playing the game, the patterns are obvious, you do not even need to look at the map to find out where you're going because you already know where the developers have set that specific scenaro to happen.To conclude, this game is very addicting, you can play for hours on end without getting bored. BUT, having said that, this game is 100% a WORKING DEVELOPMENT, only purchase this game if you are prepared to put up with some annoying bugs and repeated scenarios. This game definetly has potential. Lets just hope that the devs see what needs to be improved and act accordingly."
