76561198052582282,Recommended,318220,14440217,"Posted: 12 February, 2015",all,Lord von Fleck,"Police Quest meets SWAT meets GTA III.This is the ""right side of the law"" simulator, I always wanted many other games to be.The interaction and immersion is great. There is sooo much you can do, while capturing the day-to-day grind.  While this could become boring, it does a pretty good job capturing the realistic career-risk of any ""routine"", where even a routine traffic stop can turn suddenly violent and the player faces sudden and possible death.It is not perfect.  There areas I wish would be improved upon.  My primary issue is, there is no, ""backup"" support.  You do not have a partner, and you can't call for backup.  I feel this, could be rectified in an expansion, which, maybe we will see some day.  This shortcoming, I was able to justify with the rationale, that, the town is pretty small, it ""might"" be possible, that you are the sole law enforcer on payroll (and of course dispatch).Enjoyable game, does a great job of immersing the player in the atmosphere.  Visuals are well done in many areas.  The open-world, random citizen/criminal generation keeps the replayability going (and humorous at times... my first day on patrol, my first three suspects were woman truck drivers... immagine my shock when this cute girl in a sexy dress jumped out of her truck and pulled a gun on me...).The realistic mode really draws you in to the life & death risks of the job... you learn to rapidly eject from your car in a chase, taking up cover behind your car, very quick.  My player has died in the line of duty four times (meaning permadeath-restart from scratch), before my latest actually has survived up to LT (and still going).There is a more arcade mode... haven't played it, where death is not possible, but injury is.  This brings me to the 2nd issue I have with the game, I believe their should be a second mode, where both injury or death is possible (not always one or the other).Great game.  Hope to see more from the developer.Definitely recommend this game.10-4!"
