,Not Recommended,318220,21267506,"Posted: 16 February, 2016",all,Kallus Rourke,"If you don't wanna read the entire thing, skip to the bottom for a tl;dr version.It seems the developers removed my review.  Go figured they wanted to hide the negative review.  I was one of the first people to play this game, and I spent several months not only playing it, but being the sole community moderator.  Enforcer is an arcade-style game.  I honestly wouldn't even call it a simulator.  Yes, you play as a cop, you can pull people over, respond to calls, etc but the game is just terrible.  The graphics are bad, movement is bad, driving is bad, general physics is bad.  Essentially,EVERYTHINGabout this game is bad.For the first few hours you can enjoy it, but after that you realize how annoying the game actually is.  The AI is a joke!  The AI drivers are terrible, which reflects back on the developer for not making a decent AI.  Here's one example:  I pull over someone for running a red light and give them a ticket.  As soon as they leave the traffic stop, they do it again!  There was even one intersection where cars would always despawn coming from a certain direction.The worst part about this game is the developer and thee publisher.  Kaligus and Chris.  They try so hard to justify their inability to properly fix this game and make it worth $20.  Excuse after excuse.  ""Updates are coming."" Yet, here we are, one year later and only 3-4 updates have even been released.  Both of these people are purely incompetent.  When I was a moderator, I was the sole community-to staff interaction.  They essentially made me the public relations guy because they are TERRIBLE at talking to their community.  Since I stepped down, their communications with the communtiy has decreased to almost none!  When Chris does post, all he does is post linking to a topic that talks about an update.  Nothing else.Customization wise, you can change your lightbar to one of three options, but one of the lightbars has been broken since day one.You can choose from various different cars; from a Crown Vic to a Charger, to a Tahoe to an F150 to even a bike,You can use custom textures on vehicles that were created by the community.Finally, here's some basics.Positives:Very basic police sim.Option to use various cars.Ability to be good cop/bad cop.Negatives:Very little to no real interaction from the developer and publisher.  Community is often left in the dark.Game hasn't changed since day 1.Basic issues such as lightbar texture problem is still not fixed.Driving is very poor and arcadey, not simulation like.Ever since a recent update, the game has gotten much worse.Publisher often tries to downplay all negativity, which includes deleting negative posts.Rips off customers by making this very basic and very horrible game $20."
