n and by 2 shots in the head the person lays down. Now apparently calling an ambulance will still work out. I get a bonus for shooting someone, and another bonus for shooting the ambulance.There is about a variëty of I think 10 missions intotal in this game and bare in mind that this whole story is a more action packed optimistic version of the actual game, in that way I am making commercial for them for over-appreciating how broken it is.Pro's:-You get to be a cop-Good concept-Driving is so broken it's funCons:-Repetetive-Looks like unfinished product (yet is not in early acces)-Anything you do in this game raises no excitement whatsoeverFinal judgement: 4/10Consumer recommendation:If you're a fan of the police and simulation thing do buy this game, you might actually enjoy it. (but don't get your hopes up) Best is to wait for it to go on sale. If this does not convince you here are some games that are cheaper and way better: Fallout 3, Fallout New Vegas, Mount and blade : warband. These are games I think you might enjoy if this game drew your attention.Producer recommendation:Game should be placed under early acces if this is an unfinished product (and believe me it is). And if you do consider this product finished: Don't ask 20 euros for it, it's a far way from being worth 20 euros.[Update]Recent changes have been made in this game, bugs have been fixed and playing it is not a general dread. Yet as I keep thinking this game should not cost as much as it does, it did turn out into a good game.I did not expect the producers to adress any of the issues since it was never stated it was Early Acces, but I am glad they did it. This is a buy, but only if you like simulation combined with police.Final final recommendation: 6.5/10"
