ay, I drive out a bit away from town. If I should really call it town, more like a glorified block. I set up near a slope, that way they don't see me until it's too late. I go to get my radar and holey moley! There's tons of radars and cones in my car. I resist the urge to litter the entire area with radars and decide to just place two instead. That proves to be quite a difficult task though as the radar keeps falling over when I try to put it on the ground. After some effort and planning I manage to get a couple up anyway. A couple of people speed by, the radars automatically issues them a ticket, that's awesome tech. Suddenly this big freakin' truck comes wobbling across the road, I yell for him to stop the vehicle. He swerves into the side of my squad car and stops. I proceed to tell him to exit the vehicle and promptly does a breathalyzer test on him. He's clean. I'm pretty suspicious about the guy though so I ask for compliance, I frisk him and check his ID as well as the plates on the car. Nothing, he's clean, the truck is clean. Oh well, gotta let him go. It's not like I gotta pay the damage on my squad car by myself. Right?... Wrong. I call dispatch and they tell me to be more careful and charge me 600 bucks. I mean, c'mon.As I walk back to my freshly repaired car, dispatch calls about a kidnapping. I'm so all over that. I get in my car, blaze my sirens and drive around aimlessly. Where am I supposed to go? I start asking people if they've seen anything suspect. No one has. Dispatch calls again, says they have a possible location. 10-4. As I watch my GPS I realize that when I switch the settings from ""mini-map"" to ""overview map"", the map is rotated so they don't look the same. Very unintuitive gear they assign here. Oh well, I manage to find my way at least. I get out my car and draw my gun, I feel my adrenaline pumping. In panic I realize I can't crouch with my gun drawn, I simply can't! I'll have to manage anyway. I see them, a girl lying on the ground and a fat white guy just stands there, looking at me, before I get the chance to tell him to get on the ground, he pulls out a gun. I shoot him in the chest. He staggers but is still alive, he points the gun at me and I shoot him again, right in the chest. He staggers again but he's still standing! What kind of beast is this?! I pop off two more bullets in his chest and stomach. Still standing. One final shot and he's down. Mission complete. 200 points to me. I call an ambulance and they take both the perp and the victim away. No further investigation needed. That's efficient policework. I grab his gun from the ground and get back to stopping cars. There seems to be A LOT of drunk drivers here. One of them swerves right towards me, I panick, my life flash before my eyes and I prepare for permadeath. He crashes straight into me and comes to a complete stop, I didn't even flinch. Seems like I'm made of some tough stuff. I arrest him then I go home to sleep. Busy day."
