76561198008896731,Recommended,318220,14085666,"Posted: 20 January, 2015",all,Buddy Thunderstruck,"Overall 7/10-------------Out of the hundreds of games I've played in my life, this is the first that I've ever found to make an honest attempt at a  general Police Officer experience (excluding dreadful paperwork and and the less interesting details).  The mechanics are a bit shoddy but ultimately functional 99% of the time so it's entirely playable for long periods without running into frustrating game breaking errors.  The graphics are comparable to The Sims zoomed into ground level, nothing impressive, but again it's tolerable.What stands out in this game is the wide variety of experiences and factors taken into account for each civilian and situation you encounter.  This game makes the effort to include experiences ranging from stopping people for speeding, broken lights, and swerving suspiciously to tracking a kidnapping or a drug dealer to a specific house, requesting a warrant, then searching the location for the potentially armed criminals and evidence lying around.Personally, I consider it worth buying for $15 or less if you're intrigued and don't mind the graphics or clunky physics of a small indie game."
